        summary: "HUMA gained ~14% on a news-heavy week. On April 21, Israel\'s Ministry of Health accepted the MAA for Symvess in arterial trauma repair with a 180-day review period. On April 24, Humacyte announced it regained sole global commercial rights to Symvess by amending its distribution agreement with Fresenius Medical Care — Fresenius retains low-single-digit royalties on ex-U.S. sales. The company also appointed Jim Mercadante as Chief Commercial Officer, and announced a KOL event on April 28 focused on the hemodialysis indication. V012 Phase 3 interim data is still expected in early June.",
