        summary: "LLY fell ~4.3% this week. IQVIA data showed Foundayo (orforglipron) generated 3,707 prescriptions in its second week — significantly below oral Wegovy, which had 18,410 prescriptions in its second week. On the positive side, CMS confirmed the Medicare GLP-1 Bridge program starting July 1 at a $50/month copay for eligible beneficiaries, with Foundayo included once FDA-approved for obesity. The Trump administration shelved the BALANCE pilot over insurer pushback but extended the bridge through 2027, which was read as broadly positive for both Lilly and Novo.",
